This example will plot a Dyson Sphere using local refinement technique, in 3D
The obtained solution is saved in file "Cube.dx".

Usage:
	1. compile with make [-e debug=no];
	2. generate the mesh with easymesh as:
               $ gmsh -3 Cube.geo
	       $ gmsh2mesh Cube.msh Cube.mesh
	3. run with ./run.sh Cube.mesh n, here the second parameter n means times for the initial global refinement of mesh grids.
	4. view the obtained numerical solution with OpenDX;

